PROJETO-DE-PESQUISA.DESCRICAO-DO-PROJETO:
Technological Objectives:
* To develop collaborative virtual training environments to allow remote "Trainer"/"Trainee" to interact with each other and with virtual models of Newbridge network products;
* To evaluate the potential of VR to replace expensive equipment in satellite training centres;
* To evaluate different modelling and architecture standards for distributed virtual environments;
* To investigate methods for transmitting non-verbal and verbal clues between collaborators;
* To investigate ways of representing collaborators and shared objects in a virtual environment;
* To solve problems of synchronization between distributed shared environments;

Project Plan:
Application: Distributed World for Training on Newbridge (now Alcatel) Switches
Description: Interactive and collaborative training session among various distant users, one of which is training the others on the architecture and use of a Switch(es). This involves some coordinated manipulation of switch parts by the collaborating users, e.g., removal of a card by one and passing it to the other for discussion. Avatars will be designed to represent the users in the Virtual World, with good arm movements for manipulating objects. An audio channel is implemented, along with textual message passing among the users.

Prototype:
As a result of this project a fully functional prototype has been developed. Such prototype allows various users to get together in a 3D Collaborative Virtual Environment where an instructor may teach them how to manipulate a faulty card in an ATM switch. Such prototype aims at teletraining as clients could learn the precise steps to be followed in order to perform such operation in the real life. The prototype allows any user with Internet access to collaborate and communicate with the other parties.

